<br>
I (Ichi) had just zoned into Butcher Block on Monday when I noticed a fellow walking rather slowly and leaning forward every so often while throwing his arms out.  I quickly gathered that he was a human and that the thing beating on him was Zarchoomi (sp).  I ran up to help at first but it was too late and the fellow died.  <br>
<br>
I decided to con her and then see if she would agro me (lvl 39) She conned admirable lol and no she didnt agro.  So I tried to hail her...no luck.  About this time she wanders a bit down the road and runs into a high elf paly, im guessing, and proceeds to pound her into the ground.  I being an ogre rooted on my fellow ogre and watched as the drake and Zarchoomi lowered the boom.  This was a very quick fight though and the Pali did not last long to my dissappointment.  I was chuckling though<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
So next i stood up and stuck with Zarchoomi.  An elf fellow who was green as the grass to me came running up to me to my suprise and hailed me.  LOL He thought Zarchoomi was a PC.  Zarchoomi dropped him flat....I hardly had time to type /cheer.  I felt bad but it still cracked me up.  Then the evil side took over muhahahahah.  I just kept following her, trying to lead the deception to others.  Another dwarf died before a group of two came and finally killed her.  I cheered her on but alas she died at their hands.<br>
<br>
It was actually rather fun.  As they were low characters I know the exp loss was not significant and most people who get wacked by Zarchoomi are so adrenline pumped about seeing her they really dont mind the death.  But I had a good laugh and some rp fun.<br>
<br>
Ok thats it eheh.  Sorry if this wasnt worth the read but I said I would share it.<br>
<br>
Ichi <br>
